WEBVTT

00:08.240 --> 00:09.230
NAOMI: <i>How long,
you and her...</i>

00:09.360 --> 00:10.430
Never met her.

00:10.640 --> 00:11.676
(GASPS)

00:11.840 --> 00:13.752
Don't let him
sell the <i>Razorback.</i>

00:13.840 --> 00:14.910
MILLER: Julie?

00:15.400 --> 00:16.914
NAOMI: <i>There's nothing
we can do for her.</i>

00:17.120 --> 00:18.349
I killed the mad scientist.

00:18.520 --> 00:20.637
<i>And now we need to kill
his science experiment.</i>

00:20.720 --> 00:21.915
And how do you suppose
we do that?

00:22.040 --> 00:24.714
We're going to use that to
knock Eros right into the sun.

00:24.960 --> 00:25.996
FRED: <i>Miller's leading
the demolition team</i>

00:26.280 --> 00:28.158
<i>to plant explosives
around the docks.</i>

00:28.400 --> 00:29.834
- (BEEPING)
- Big problem, <i>pampa.</i>

00:30.120 --> 00:31.520
Detonator safety got fried.

00:31.880 --> 00:33.997
Sixty-second reset.
Best we can do.

00:34.440 --> 00:36.671
- (BEEPING STOPS)
- Go. Get back to the ship.

00:36.880 --> 00:38.792
Miller, answer me.
Are you all right?

00:43.200 --> 00:45.192
Guys? What the hell
just happened?

00:45.280 --> 00:46.634
The <i>Nauvoo</i> just missed!

00:46.880 --> 00:50.510
The <i>Nauvoo</i> didn't move,
Miller. Eros did.

00:52.200 --> 00:54.271
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

01:53.520 --> 01:54.920
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

02:06.280 --> 02:08.157
MILLER: Is it
something I said?

02:09.039 --> 02:11.236
Maybe now's a good time
to get off this rock.

02:11.640 --> 02:12.630
NAOMI: <i>Miller, you're moving.</i>

02:12.800 --> 02:15.713
I mean,
Eros is moving. Fast.

02:20.000 --> 02:21.036
JANUS: Excuse me.

02:21.160 --> 02:23.356
- I got some crackpot report...
- Eros.

02:23.440 --> 02:25.477
The whole damn asteroid is
moving under its own power.

02:25.560 --> 02:28.120
It's not exactly possible,
yet that's what we've got.

02:28.480 --> 02:29.596
Moving to where?

02:30.040 --> 02:32.077
Unknown. But it's
de-orbiting sunward.

02:32.400 --> 02:33.720
- Do we know why?
- We do not.

02:34.240 --> 02:36.471
The Mormon generation ship
was heading for Eros

02:36.560 --> 02:37.676
before the incident?

02:37.800 --> 02:39.996
Fred Johnson claimed
it was an engine test.

02:40.080 --> 02:42.356
But given the <i>Nauvoo's</i>
speed and trajectory,

02:42.480 --> 02:45.154
it was on a collision course
with Eros. Which means,

02:45.240 --> 02:46.230
he's lying to us.

02:46.560 --> 02:48.631
Madam, the Mormon
leadership in Salt Lake

02:48.720 --> 02:50.677
is claiming Johnson
stole the <i>Nauvoo</i>

02:50.760 --> 02:52.638
after forcibly removing
all their people

02:52.720 --> 02:53.915
from the ship.

02:54.280 --> 02:55.760
Tell me,
Colonel Janus.

02:55.840 --> 02:59.550
How does a big rock like Eros
suddenly turn into a ship?

02:59.640 --> 03:01.518
Madam,
I don't know.

03:02.200 --> 03:04.112
If Eros stopped rotating
that quick,

03:04.200 --> 03:06.192
I'd be dead as a bug
on a windshield.

03:07.120 --> 03:10.158
Uh, okay. So we broke
a few laws of physics here.

03:10.600 --> 03:12.159
Maybe God's trying
to play a magic trick?

03:12.680 --> 03:15.434
Eros is what, 7,000 trillion
kilos, give or take?

03:15.720 --> 03:17.473
Its temperature's
gone up two degrees.

03:17.840 --> 03:20.639
Yeah, it's putting out...
(MUTTERING)

03:20.960 --> 03:22.474
- Around 10 exajoules.
- Yeah.

03:22.560 --> 03:24.358
That's the energy
of a two-gigaton bomb.

03:24.880 --> 03:26.200
AMOS: You couldn't
move Eros like that

03:26.280 --> 03:28.431
- with a two-gigaton blast.
- NAOMI: No.

03:28.560 --> 03:30.392
I think we're looking
at the waste heat,

03:30.520 --> 03:32.352
which means the laws of
thermodynamics still hold.

03:32.480 --> 03:33.709
<i>At least we still have that.</i>

03:33.800 --> 03:35.473
If Eros isn't
spinning anymore,

03:35.560 --> 03:37.119
then how can I still
have gravity?

03:37.480 --> 03:40.473
Dresden said the protomolecule
would break all the rules.

03:40.560 --> 03:42.711
Yeah, he also
said that stuff...

03:42.800 --> 03:44.632
It's not from around here.

03:44.720 --> 03:46.473
So, who the heck are we
to say what it's capable of?

03:48.240 --> 03:49.276
(MONITOR BEEPING)

03:50.800 --> 03:52.120
Oh, shit.

03:53.000 --> 03:55.720
- Alex?
- It's that damn rock.

03:55.800 --> 03:57.234
It's speeding up.

03:58.440 --> 04:00.432
It's in a heck of a hurry
to get somewhere.

04:02.120 --> 04:03.918
You know,
I don't feel any acceleration,

04:04.000 --> 04:06.834
but, man, it sure looks like I'm
leaving you guys in the dust.

04:06.920 --> 04:09.435
Hang tight there, <i>amigo.</i>
We are tracking you.

04:10.000 --> 04:11.559
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

04:13.960 --> 04:18.829
So, uh, I guess that
rescue plan's put on hold.

04:19.200 --> 04:20.519
We're working
on a contingency.

04:21.200 --> 04:23.476
Okay, good, 'cause for
a second there I thought

04:23.560 --> 04:25.677
maybe we'd lost control
of the situation.

04:28.560 --> 04:29.914
We have to embrace the
obvious conclusion,

04:30.040 --> 04:31.599
that Eros is some
kind of weapon system

04:31.680 --> 04:33.114
unlike anything
we've seen.

04:33.200 --> 04:34.429
Ah, yes,
a weapon.

04:34.520 --> 04:36.751
A hammer thinks
everything is a nail.

04:36.920 --> 04:39.560
- I assume, built by Mars.
- Who else?

04:39.640 --> 04:41.438
They provoke a conventional
war as a smokescreen,

04:41.520 --> 04:43.352
then hurl
this thing at us.

04:44.880 --> 04:46.030
Anything from Mars?

04:46.120 --> 04:48.191
There's nothing but
denials and confusion.

04:48.440 --> 04:50.272
- (BEEPING)
- What's happening?

04:50.360 --> 04:53.478
Eros has changed
trajectory again.

04:53.560 --> 04:54.880
And it's accelerating.

04:57.600 --> 05:00.672
It's now on a direct
collision course with Earth.

05:05.720 --> 05:07.712
(DETONATOR BEEPING STOPS)

05:09.040 --> 05:10.633
I've disarmed all the
bombs on the surface.

05:11.440 --> 05:12.840
Still working
on yours, Miller.

05:13.120 --> 05:15.396
Yup. My bomb
has to be special.

05:16.800 --> 05:18.439
SADAVIR: <i>Jules-Pierre Mao.</i>

05:19.760 --> 05:23.674
Looks like your attempts
to keep Eros under the radar

05:24.280 --> 05:26.078
has hit a few snags.

05:30.360 --> 05:32.920
You call yourself
a "man of the system,"

05:33.000 --> 05:36.072
but I'm not.
Earth is my home.

05:36.800 --> 05:39.031
So whenever you're ready,
I'd really appreciate it

05:39.120 --> 05:40.793
if you'd make
a fucking appearance,

05:40.880 --> 05:43.315
and rein in your
goddamn science experiment!

05:44.080 --> 05:45.070
(CLATTERING)

05:53.440 --> 05:54.430
(BEEPING)

05:55.640 --> 05:57.597
It's still not responding.
Hang in there.

06:04.920 --> 06:07.230
AMOS: That massive heat spike
before Eros moved?

06:07.840 --> 06:09.672
What if that's
the "seed crystal"

06:09.760 --> 06:11.274
that creepy guy
was talking about?

06:11.360 --> 06:13.238
That's the engine
that's moving Eros.

06:14.640 --> 06:16.120
I have a terrible idea.

06:16.200 --> 06:18.795
If Miller can get in there,
close, with that warhead,

06:18.880 --> 06:21.270
he could kill it.
Stop Eros in its tracks.

06:22.000 --> 06:23.912
HOLDEN: Or unleash
something worse.

06:24.000 --> 06:25.036
Eros just dodged
the <i>Nauvoo</i> with a shrug.

06:25.120 --> 06:27.237
What's it going to do when he
crawls inside there with a nuke?

06:27.520 --> 06:28.840
MILLER: <i>There's only
one way to find out.</i>

06:29.680 --> 06:31.000
NAOMI: What do
you think, Miller?

06:31.600 --> 06:34.320
<i>Crawl in there and blow up
the thing that ate Julie?</i>

06:34.880 --> 06:37.998
I think it's the best bad idea
I've heard all day.

06:39.360 --> 06:41.317
NAOMI: We need to figure out
that dead man's switch,

06:41.400 --> 06:43.392
create a longer delay so that
we can get you out of there

06:43.480 --> 06:45.711
before the bomb detonates.
I'm on it.

06:45.840 --> 06:47.320
<i>There's the spirit, kid.</i>

06:47.680 --> 06:50.240
I'm gonna take
my pet nuke for a walk

06:50.320 --> 06:52.198
and see what's what.

06:52.280 --> 06:53.953
Why don't you guys
try to map me out

06:54.040 --> 06:56.157
the shortest way to get
to where I'm going.

06:56.440 --> 06:58.238
Oh, we'll be ready
once you're inside.

06:58.400 --> 07:02.030
(GRUNTS) Come on.
It's just you and me now, kid.

07:02.400 --> 07:03.390
To hell.

07:04.640 --> 07:05.960
A rock three times
the size of the one

07:06.040 --> 07:07.713
that wiped out
the dinosaurs.

07:08.160 --> 07:10.277
But given Eros' erratic
speed and acceleration,

07:10.360 --> 07:12.079
we really don't know
where it's going to hit.

07:13.240 --> 07:16.199
Latest projection,
seven to 10 billion dead.

07:18.640 --> 07:21.314
Another 10 in the aftermath
of environmental disaster.

07:24.360 --> 07:25.510
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

07:25.600 --> 07:27.353
We have to
begin evacuation,

07:27.440 --> 07:30.000
use every available
ship and transport.

07:30.200 --> 07:31.793
We'll need
a lottery system,

07:31.880 --> 07:33.712
and to control
public hysteria.

07:33.920 --> 07:35.400
There's only
one option left.

07:36.400 --> 07:37.800
Our planetary defenses.

07:38.240 --> 07:40.197
A massive missile
launch at Eros.

07:40.280 --> 07:42.192
NGUYEN: The odds are good
that we'd destroy it.

07:42.360 --> 07:43.760
Or at least turn it into
a million pebbles.

07:43.840 --> 07:45.194
Whatever biotoxin
is inside Eros,

07:45.560 --> 07:47.199
can it survive in a vacuum?
Or do we risk scattering it

07:47.320 --> 07:48.470
all over the system?

07:48.560 --> 07:50.074
Sadly,
there's no time to conduct a study

07:50.160 --> 07:51.992
to satisfy
your curiosity.

07:55.720 --> 07:57.074
We'll sterilize
the detonation zone

07:57.160 --> 07:58.514
with a second wave
of missiles.

08:04.080 --> 08:05.719
Ready the arsenal.

08:08.160 --> 08:11.039
And get the Secretary a line
to the Martian Prime Minister.

08:11.160 --> 08:12.435
We don't want
them mistaking

08:12.520 --> 08:14.239
our missiles
for a first strike.

08:16.280 --> 08:19.159
Let's hope they're feeling
warm and fuzzy today.

08:20.320 --> 08:23.438
(GRUNTS) I'm almost
to the air lock.

08:24.160 --> 08:27.995
I didn't count on this damn
bomb loving gravity so much.

08:28.080 --> 08:29.230
(MILLER GASPING)

08:30.120 --> 08:31.918
- (THUDDING)
- (PANTING)

08:38.720 --> 08:40.712
There's alien life
in the universe,

08:41.080 --> 08:44.756
and I'm riding it,
like a tick on a dog.

08:45.120 --> 08:47.191
NAOMI: <i>Hey, don't get
all "Holden" on me.</i>

08:47.600 --> 08:49.239
Weird and chatty
under pressure.

08:49.440 --> 08:50.510
MILLER: <i>Yeah.</i>

08:50.800 --> 08:53.599
Must be real tough
growin' up under a blue sky...

08:55.400 --> 08:57.790
Eight parents slobbering
all over you.

08:58.080 --> 09:00.390
NAOMI: Hey, now. Wait till
you get to know him better.

09:00.880 --> 09:02.030
<i>He's got lots of layers.</i>

09:02.200 --> 09:04.351
MILLER: Yeah.
So does a rock tunnel.

09:06.120 --> 09:07.270
Naomi.

09:09.200 --> 09:10.759
What are the chances
of getting him outta there

09:10.840 --> 09:11.956
once he plants that nuke?

09:13.280 --> 09:15.795
I help him rig a timer to get
around that dead man's switch.

09:15.880 --> 09:18.634
He backtracks to the docks.
We swoop in and get him.

09:18.960 --> 09:21.270
HOLDEN: We need time to clear
the blast radius if he's late...

09:21.360 --> 09:22.350
ALEX: Hey, easy there, Chief.

09:22.440 --> 09:23.590
You do realize that
docking with Eros

09:23.680 --> 09:24.875
ain't gonna be
a cakewalk, right?

09:25.000 --> 09:26.070
That's a moving target.

09:26.160 --> 09:28.516
That station so much as twitches
while we're swooping in,

09:28.600 --> 09:30.990
they're gonna be sendin'
what's left of us home in a doggie bag.

09:31.080 --> 09:32.958
He's risking his ass
down there.

09:33.040 --> 09:35.077
How about we do
the same up here?

09:40.880 --> 09:42.997
(PANTING)

09:47.200 --> 09:49.760
MILLER: <i>This guy's friends
were probably infected.</i>

09:50.520 --> 09:52.477
<i>They would've spread it
if you let them get away.</i>

09:54.000 --> 09:55.320
It was the right call.

09:56.360 --> 09:57.760
What makes you think
it's not gonna do

09:57.840 --> 10:00.116
the same thing to you
the second you walk in there?

10:05.160 --> 10:06.196
(GRUNTS)

10:07.680 --> 10:09.080
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

10:12.160 --> 10:14.117
(GROANING)

10:18.200 --> 10:20.032
Remember me? (CHUCKLES)

10:22.360 --> 10:25.558
Yeah. I missed you, too.

10:33.640 --> 10:34.960
(GRUNTS)

10:42.480 --> 10:43.709
Okay.

10:54.480 --> 10:55.914
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

11:00.440 --> 11:01.954
(BEEPING STOPS)

11:13.920 --> 11:15.513
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

11:17.800 --> 11:19.553
In all your years,
did you imagine

11:19.640 --> 11:21.233
you'd see
a moment like this?

11:25.600 --> 11:27.353
The Martian Prime Minister
confirmed.

11:28.280 --> 11:30.749
They won't consider our
launch a pre-emptive strike.

11:32.960 --> 11:34.440
Nor did they
offer assistance.

11:34.800 --> 11:36.951
Maybe they want to see how
well their weapon performs.

11:37.520 --> 11:39.751
Or to watch
how ours fails.

11:48.520 --> 11:52.196
Sir. Silos are open.

12:20.520 --> 12:22.432
- (GRUNTS)
- (DETONATOR BEEPING)

12:42.240 --> 12:43.640
(BEEPING INTENSIFIES)

12:52.920 --> 12:54.832
- (BEEPING STOPS)
- (PANTING)

13:00.680 --> 13:02.353
(GRUNTING)

13:16.160 --> 13:17.913
There's a body.

13:18.000 --> 13:21.437
Doesn't seem to be infected
at all. That's weird.

13:40.400 --> 13:41.550
(GRUNTING)

13:45.920 --> 13:47.798
FEMALE VOICE:
<i>Gone and gone, and gone...</i>

13:47.880 --> 13:50.270
What was that?
Naomi, I didn't catch that.

13:50.360 --> 13:52.591
Miller, I didn't
say anything.

13:54.200 --> 13:55.600
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

13:58.440 --> 13:59.715
(BEEPING STOPS)

14:04.440 --> 14:06.352
Guess I must be going
the right way.

14:07.000 --> 14:11.040
Steady on, Miller.
Service exit, to your left.

14:11.960 --> 14:13.076
You hanging in there?

14:13.160 --> 14:14.230
MILLER: <i>Oh, yeah. Good times.</i>

14:14.720 --> 14:16.473
Think I might stop by
for some barbecue

14:16.560 --> 14:19.314
down on the main level
after this.

14:20.160 --> 14:21.799
Well, it's, uh...

14:22.600 --> 14:24.478
I can't shake the feeling
I'm being watched.

14:24.720 --> 14:28.430
<i>That's me. I'm watching you.
You're doin' great.</i>

14:29.000 --> 14:31.071
Yeah. That must be it.

14:31.160 --> 14:32.230
(INDISTINCT MALE VOICES)

14:33.240 --> 14:35.391
<i>These voices are...</i>

14:35.520 --> 14:36.954
They're not
alive, Miller.

14:37.040 --> 14:39.430
They're just echoes
of who those people were.

14:42.960 --> 14:44.997
(INDISTINCT MALE VOICES)

15:02.480 --> 15:05.871
MILLER: You know what?
I think it's leaving the dead alone.

15:09.880 --> 15:12.440
Seems like it still has
some use for the living.

15:13.160 --> 15:14.799
NAOMI: Don't wanna know
what that's about.

15:16.920 --> 15:18.070
(THUDDING)

15:18.560 --> 15:22.440
Oh, crap. Looks like I'm gonna
need a minute here, guys.

15:33.520 --> 15:34.510
(BEEPING)

15:47.360 --> 15:48.953
So it goes.

15:57.720 --> 16:00.280
We had to expect a launch.
It was the only move.

16:01.040 --> 16:02.997
That's it. We should
pull Miller out now.

16:06.640 --> 16:07.630
(GRUNTS)

16:13.480 --> 16:15.392
Guys, what's going
on out there?

16:15.560 --> 16:16.710
HOLDEN: <i>Funny you should ask.</i>

16:17.360 --> 16:19.317
Earth just launched half
her nuclear arsenal,

16:19.400 --> 16:22.074
and I'm guessing they just
target-locked Eros Station.

16:23.920 --> 16:25.036
Oh.

16:26.080 --> 16:29.676
Are you sure
that's a good idea?

16:29.880 --> 16:31.917
HOLDEN: <i>Well, the UN
didn't check with us first.</i>

16:32.080 --> 16:34.470
But it does mean you're going to
need to pick up the pace down there.

16:45.600 --> 16:47.080
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

16:47.800 --> 16:48.995
(BEEPING)

16:49.240 --> 16:51.516
- What the <i>xelep</i> now?
- Where's Eros?

16:51.680 --> 16:52.670
I can't find it.

16:53.880 --> 16:56.600
Holden, we just lost
radar lock on Eros.

16:56.840 --> 16:58.513
The whole damn station
just vanished.

16:59.000 --> 17:00.673
HOLDEN: Acknowledged, Tycho.
It's off our radar, too.

17:00.760 --> 17:03.036
But it's still right there.
We have visual.

17:03.120 --> 17:06.715
It's just...
It's just not reflecting radar anymore.

17:10.920 --> 17:13.719
So if Earth's missiles
can't see Eros...

17:14.119 --> 17:16.191
Then they can't
blow it up.

17:23.359 --> 17:25.032
(STATIC)

17:31.560 --> 17:33.279
(DOOR BEEPING, UNLOCKS)

17:35.120 --> 17:37.157
- (EXHALES)
- (DOOR LOCKS)

17:38.320 --> 17:41.996
Eros is moving towards Earth.
On its own.

17:44.520 --> 17:46.318
What can you tell me
about that?

17:47.840 --> 17:51.959
The flower is unfolding.
It's becoming.

17:52.680 --> 17:55.479
- How can we stop it?
- I've no idea.

17:55.880 --> 17:57.917
Why would you
want to stop it?

17:59.800 --> 18:02.554
Our missiles have lost
their target locks.

18:05.000 --> 18:07.640
How do you lose a target
the size of a goddamn moon?

18:07.720 --> 18:10.679
Eros vanished off radar.
It's gone stealth.

18:11.960 --> 18:13.189
Who's going to
explain that to me?

18:13.520 --> 18:15.716
Our missiles, sir.
They're flying blind.

18:15.840 --> 18:17.957
Which makes them
essentially useless.

18:18.040 --> 18:19.872
Incoming strong-message
from Fred Johnson

18:20.000 --> 18:21.195
on the emergency channel.

18:21.360 --> 18:23.716
Fred Johnson?
Does he have something to do with this?

18:24.600 --> 18:27.718
<i>UN Security Council,
I have been monitoring</i>

18:27.800 --> 18:30.918
<i>this incredible
situation on Eros,</i>

18:31.000 --> 18:32.832
<i>and believe I
have a solution.</i>

18:33.360 --> 18:36.592
<i>The OPA has a ship
in visual range of Eros,</i>

18:36.680 --> 18:39.434
<i>that can use its
laser-guidance system</i>

18:39.520 --> 18:41.876
<i>to paint the target
for your missiles.</i>

18:42.040 --> 18:43.918
<i>But given the signal
delay to Earth,</i>

18:44.000 --> 18:47.118
<i>my technicians would need
to steer the missiles in.</i>

18:47.880 --> 18:50.520
<i>I understand the gravity
of the request,</i>

18:50.600 --> 18:52.273
<i>but need a
response before</i>

18:52.400 --> 18:54.392
<i>the window
of opportunity closes.</i>

18:55.400 --> 18:58.552
This is exactly the kind of
opportunity he's been waiting for.

18:58.880 --> 19:01.520
He could redirect our
missiles at Mars. Or Earth.

19:01.600 --> 19:03.034
CHRISJEN: It's just
the guidance systems.

19:03.400 --> 19:05.073
We still have
our abort codes.

19:05.240 --> 19:06.720
Besides, why would he?

19:06.800 --> 19:09.269
The Belt dies
without Earth and Mars.

19:09.360 --> 19:10.430
Because he's got
blood on his hands.

19:10.520 --> 19:12.239
He's a mad terrorist.
Your words.

19:12.400 --> 19:14.392
I need a moment.

19:16.960 --> 19:18.553
Can you see this
OPA ship?

19:18.920 --> 19:21.674
Not in the wake of Eros.
It's radar-dark, too.

19:21.760 --> 19:23.513
We'll have to take Fred
Johnson's word for it.

19:23.640 --> 19:26.678
CHRISJEN: Or I could talk to the
captain of this ship directly.

19:26.920 --> 19:29.560
Any message would have to be
relayed through Tycho Station.

19:29.720 --> 19:31.040
Open a channel.

19:36.080 --> 19:38.390
MILLER: These things are starting
to take a real likin' to me.

19:39.360 --> 19:41.079
If they get
inside this suit,

19:41.200 --> 19:43.510
I won't have to worry
about Earth's nukes.

19:44.360 --> 19:46.431
Doin' good.
Think happy thoughts.

19:47.920 --> 19:51.277
Happy thoughts.
That's good. Happy thoughts.

19:52.280 --> 19:53.396
(GRUNTING)

19:53.960 --> 19:55.189
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

20:00.600 --> 20:02.273
(BEEPING STOPS)

20:04.880 --> 20:06.030
(VOICE BREAKING) Roci...

20:06.120 --> 20:09.397
Miller, your feed's
crapping out again. Miller?

20:10.280 --> 20:16.277
- (STATIC INTERFERENCE)
- Repeat, <i>Roci.</i> Repeat <i>. Roci.</i>

20:21.080 --> 20:23.072
Well, I'll just keep following
the heat, I guess.

20:26.960 --> 20:29.520
Miller, come in.

20:30.160 --> 20:32.152
(MONITOR BEEPING)

20:32.840 --> 20:36.311
<i>Captain. In this
terrible hour,</i>

20:36.400 --> 20:38.392
<i>I appeal to
your humanity.</i>

20:38.480 --> 20:41.200
(INDISTINCT VOICES)

20:41.640 --> 20:43.233
JULIE: <i>You can't
take the</i> Razorback.

20:43.320 --> 20:45.630
You're not alive.
You're not alive.

20:45.720 --> 20:48.440
There's no one here.
Just voices.

20:48.520 --> 20:50.637
Sick. Talking to myself.

20:50.720 --> 20:51.915
(INDISTINCT VOICES)

20:53.840 --> 20:55.115
(BEEPING)

20:56.960 --> 20:59.077
<i>Madam Avasarala,
I'm James Holden,</i>

20:59.160 --> 21:01.152
<i>captain of the</i> Rocinante.

21:01.280 --> 21:04.671
<i>I've seen firsthand the hell
that's going on inside Eros,</i>

21:04.760 --> 21:06.752
<i>and it mustn't be allowed
to reach Earth.</i>

21:07.240 --> 21:09.197
<i>Fred Johnson
is honorable.</i>

21:09.280 --> 21:10.509
<i>Give him access
to your missiles,</i>

21:10.600 --> 21:12.990
<i>and my crew and I
will guide them in.</i>

21:13.080 --> 21:14.719
<i>There's no time
to bargain.</i>

21:14.800 --> 21:16.473
<i>We can only choose
to trust each other.</i>

21:16.840 --> 21:18.638
<i>I pray that we will.</i>

21:19.880 --> 21:22.156
Good thing
the assassins missed.

21:23.680 --> 21:25.160
We can't
trust this man.

21:26.360 --> 21:28.192
Sir, James Holden
is neck-deep

21:28.280 --> 21:29.999
in everything
that's happening.

21:30.080 --> 21:32.231
He's Fred Johnson's
puppet.

21:32.320 --> 21:33.993
On any other day
this discussion

21:34.080 --> 21:35.639
would get us
shot for treason,

21:35.760 --> 21:38.070
then thrown
into a lunatic asylum.

21:38.720 --> 21:41.554
Give them guidance control of the missiles,
Mr. Secretary.

21:41.840 --> 21:44.992
I vouch for James Holden.
We can trust him.

21:48.880 --> 21:51.679
What the caterpillar
calls the end of the world,

21:53.200 --> 21:55.396
the master
calls a butterfly.

22:12.080 --> 22:13.673
Alex, how we doing
on that target lock?

22:14.680 --> 22:16.000
Target is
still painted, Chief.

22:17.040 --> 22:18.759
Let's try the S-band.
Patch it.

22:23.240 --> 22:27.951
Miller, come in!
Miller!

22:28.120 --> 22:29.998
MILLER: <i>Hey!
Trying to blow my eardrums?</i>

22:30.080 --> 22:31.833
Listen,
you need to move your ass in there.

22:32.440 --> 22:34.033
Earth's missiles are
headed for Eros,

22:34.120 --> 22:35.270
and we're painting
the bull's-eye.

22:35.440 --> 22:36.840
Don't put us in the
really awkward position

22:36.920 --> 22:38.434
of having to
blow you up.

22:38.560 --> 22:41.394
You know, there was a time
not too long ago,

22:41.480 --> 22:44.075
I would've been rooting
for Eros over those missiles.

22:44.240 --> 22:46.960
I know what you mean,
<i>beltalowda.</i> Now, move.

22:47.040 --> 22:48.076
MILLER: <i>Yes, sir.</i>

22:49.960 --> 22:54.239
150 live thermonuclear
missiles under your control.

22:55.160 --> 22:58.232
I believe that makes you the most
powerful man in the system right now.

22:58.320 --> 23:01.631
Oh, really?
Then go get me a cup of coffee.

23:03.200 --> 23:05.078
- (CHUCKLES)
- (MONITOR BEEPING)

23:05.400 --> 23:10.031
<i>Felotas!</i> Eros is accelerating again.
It's surging.

23:10.960 --> 23:14.112
I'm starting to think Eros doesn't like being
followed or having things pointed at it.

23:14.520 --> 23:15.920
Do not lose visual!

23:16.320 --> 23:17.720
We're already
burning hot as it is.

23:17.800 --> 23:19.871
You wanna go flat-out,
the <i>Roci</i> can handle it,

23:20.000 --> 23:21.559
but you gotta understand,
you burn like that,

23:21.640 --> 23:23.632
at some point,
we're not gonna be around to enjoy the ride.

23:23.880 --> 23:24.916
What's the limit?

23:25.000 --> 23:26.320
ALEX: <i>I don't know.
Maybe 15, 20 Gs?</i>

23:26.680 --> 23:28.433
We could probably handle that
if we're juiced to the gills,

23:28.520 --> 23:32.230
but eventually one of those little blood
vessels in your brain's gonna go pop.

23:32.320 --> 23:34.596
The <i>Roci</i> will stay with you on auto-pilot,
long as it takes.

23:34.680 --> 23:35.955
MILLER: <i>Keeping
the welcome mat out</i>

23:36.040 --> 23:37.793
<i>for a couple 100
nuclear missiles, huh?</i>

23:37.880 --> 23:39.837
That's the situation.
So beat us to it, Miller,

23:39.920 --> 23:42.594
and we can all go home.
I'll even give you a ride.

23:42.760 --> 23:45.514
All right. A good bottle
of Ganymede gin.

23:46.000 --> 23:47.878
Whoever doesn't
stop Eros is buying.

23:50.160 --> 23:51.435
All right.
You're on.

23:51.520 --> 23:54.718
In other news, I think I'm getting
close to that hot zone of Naomi's.

23:56.280 --> 23:57.270
Excuse me?

23:57.360 --> 23:58.510
Seed crystal.

23:58.880 --> 24:00.109
Oh. Right.

24:00.360 --> 24:02.238
- (MONITOR BEEPING)
- HOLDEN: Oh, shit.

24:03.840 --> 24:05.957
All right, Hoss.
Eros is movin' away.

24:06.360 --> 24:08.511
You gotta call it.
Chase, or cut bait?

24:19.160 --> 24:20.230
Captain?

24:23.080 --> 24:24.673
Strap in. Prep to
match speed.

24:24.760 --> 24:26.160
You got it.

24:26.880 --> 24:28.360
- ALEX: All clear?
- HOLDEN: Clear.

24:29.320 --> 24:32.233
All right,
cowboys and cowgirl.

24:32.760 --> 24:33.876
Here comes the juice.

24:35.720 --> 24:37.120
(GRUNTING)

24:47.520 --> 24:50.672
Incoming from the <i>Rocinante,</i>
13-minute transmission delay.

24:50.920 --> 24:54.152
The ship is ramping to a 15-G burn
to match speed with the target.

24:54.240 --> 24:56.550
It will auto-lock on Eros
for the missiles.

24:57.320 --> 25:00.597
Survivability of the crew is
questionable beyond this point.

25:02.440 --> 25:07.037
They're going to stay with Eros,
even if it kills them.

25:11.760 --> 25:13.080
Your evac
shuttle is ready.

25:13.360 --> 25:15.079
There's nothing left
to do here.

25:15.240 --> 25:17.914
The Secretary General and most
of the others are already gone.

25:19.280 --> 25:20.475
One more minute.

25:21.440 --> 25:23.591
(SIGHS) Yeah.

25:32.440 --> 25:34.830
- Arjun?
<i>- How are you holding up?</i>

25:35.920 --> 25:38.515
Acid stomach. And ravenous
for a big thick steak...

25:38.640 --> 25:40.597
<i>I assume they'll be evacuating
you here to Luna. I'm sorry,</i>

25:40.680 --> 25:42.911
<i>I spoke over you.
This damn delay...</i>

25:43.360 --> 25:45.636
Arjun, I need
to stay here.

25:45.920 --> 25:49.118
- I can't let...
<i>- Yes. I expected you'd say that.</i>

25:49.480 --> 25:50.630
- No.
<i>- Yes, I...</i>

25:50.800 --> 25:51.790
- Wait...
<i>- No.</i>

25:51.920 --> 25:54.071
- Wait, listen...
<i>- Wait, me first.</i>

25:54.160 --> 25:56.550
<i>- Please.</i>
- All right.

25:56.920 --> 25:58.274
<i>And let
me finish.</i>

26:01.320 --> 26:03.516
<i>I've been rehearsing
this moment for years,</i>

26:03.640 --> 26:06.678
<i>but now that
it's here, I'm lost.</i>

26:10.480 --> 26:13.996
<i>I smiled and grinned
when you took that trip</i>

26:14.120 --> 26:17.397
<i>to the Sinai battlefront.
I put on a good face</i>

26:17.480 --> 26:19.995
<i>when you almost died
in that transport from Pallas.</i>

26:22.160 --> 26:25.631
<i>- I even...</i>
- Yes, and that is what I love about you.

26:25.720 --> 26:27.120
<i>Oh, God damn it!</i>

26:27.200 --> 26:30.034
I know it has
never been easy.

26:30.120 --> 26:31.759
I know that.
And I'm sorry...

26:31.840 --> 26:34.878
<i>Stop it. Stop.</i>

26:36.960 --> 26:38.519
<i>You never have to
apologize to me.</i>

26:40.840 --> 26:41.830
Sorry.

26:43.120 --> 26:45.760
Just know,
I want to be there with you,

26:45.840 --> 26:48.674
and help you with
that sad little garden.

26:49.800 --> 26:53.760
But our home is threatened,
and if I left...

26:53.880 --> 26:55.872
You wouldn't
respect me anyway.

26:59.720 --> 27:02.474
<i>Why did I marry
such a great woman?</i>

27:03.720 --> 27:06.758
You got very lucky.
Didn't you?

27:39.920 --> 27:41.593
(INDISTINCT VOICES)

27:46.280 --> 27:47.953
Gotta be close now.

27:54.120 --> 27:56.157
Real gentle,
this last stretch.

27:56.880 --> 27:59.873
Another 50 meters
or so. (GASPING)

28:00.120 --> 28:02.760
So far the station hasn't
considered you a threat.

28:03.160 --> 28:04.753
<i>Let's keep it that way.</i>

28:07.120 --> 28:09.396
FEMALE VOICE: <i>And it's gone
and gone and gone...</i>

28:11.040 --> 28:12.793
<i>Can't take the</i> Razorback...

28:20.840 --> 28:22.274
(RAPID BEEPING)

28:23.800 --> 28:24.950
(GROANING)

28:26.200 --> 28:29.113
Slow down, you ornery
son of a bitch.

28:33.800 --> 28:34.836
(EXCLAIMS)

28:35.640 --> 28:37.120
There goes my spleen.

28:37.280 --> 28:38.430
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.

28:42.240 --> 28:44.550
- (BEEPING)
- (GRUNTS)

28:44.640 --> 28:45.835
Sorry about this, guys.

28:48.560 --> 28:49.630
(GASPING)

28:54.080 --> 28:55.070
Gotcha!

28:58.720 --> 29:00.916
(INDISTINCT VOICES)

29:08.240 --> 29:09.879
JULIE: <i>Can't take
the</i> Razorback...

29:10.960 --> 29:12.030
<i>Razorback.</i>

29:13.840 --> 29:16.150
JULIE: <i>Catch me if you can.</i>

29:16.240 --> 29:18.277
<i>And it's gone, gone, gone...</i>

29:18.880 --> 29:21.156
- (INDISTINCT VOICES)
- Naomi.

29:21.640 --> 29:23.518
<i>Can you check the
med-data on my suit?</i>

29:24.160 --> 29:25.719
NAOMI: (GRUNTS) You're fine.

29:26.080 --> 29:28.151
- I mean, for you.
- What's going on?

29:28.480 --> 29:31.632
I just don't want you to think
I'm hallucinating or anything.

29:31.920 --> 29:32.990
Okay. Go.

29:33.080 --> 29:34.480
MILLER: <i>You know
those voices I'm hearing?</i>

29:35.080 --> 29:38.756
I think this thing has
taken the, I don't know,

29:38.880 --> 29:41.714
consciousness,
some part of whatever

29:41.840 --> 29:45.356
it is that makes us human.
It's eating it,

29:46.200 --> 29:49.193
spitting it back out in some
other configuration.

29:49.280 --> 29:50.475
HOLDEN: Miller, we don't
have time for this!

29:50.880 --> 29:53.714
Naomi's heat map. You know
where it's leading us?

29:54.560 --> 29:56.711
It's leading us right back
to the Blue Falcon.

29:57.280 --> 29:58.555
HOLDEN: <i>Where we found Julie?</i>

29:58.640 --> 30:00.040
MILLER: I mean,
what are the chances, right?

30:00.840 --> 30:03.719
These voices are getting louder
the closer I get to there.

30:03.840 --> 30:04.990
Okay.

30:07.040 --> 30:08.554
I think she's
still in there.

30:08.720 --> 30:10.677
Miller, Julie Mao's dead.
We both saw her.

30:10.760 --> 30:12.956
<i>Yeah, what does dead mean
to a protomolecule, right?</i>

30:13.400 --> 30:15.073
I'm not talking
about her body.

30:15.160 --> 30:17.834
I mean, her...
Her consciousness.

30:18.320 --> 30:22.109
<i>I'm talking about a part of her
that might be a part of this rock.</i>

30:22.280 --> 30:25.512
- Jesus!<i>
- Everything happening here is all built around Julie.</i>

30:26.240 --> 30:28.516
Julie was the first one
to get infected.

30:30.080 --> 30:32.231
And it was right there
at the Blue Falcon.

30:32.880 --> 30:35.236
The protomolecule
infected her.

30:35.560 --> 30:39.190
What if, she infected
the protomolecule back.

30:40.000 --> 30:43.596
You know the <i>Razorback,</i> her old ship,
headed right for Earth?

30:44.120 --> 30:46.077
I keep hearing her talk
about the <i>Razorback.</i>

30:46.160 --> 30:47.594
I think she thinks
she's on it.

30:48.200 --> 30:50.317
<i>I think she's controlling
this whole thing.</i>

30:51.960 --> 30:53.474
She's the seed crystal.

30:54.240 --> 30:55.560
(CRUMBLING)

30:56.600 --> 30:58.114
HOLDEN: <i>Miller? What the
hell's happening down there?</i>

30:58.360 --> 30:59.430
Stop chasing Eros!

30:59.640 --> 31:00.676
I can't do that!

31:00.840 --> 31:02.433
Tap the brakes,
then, asshole!

31:02.800 --> 31:04.439
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

31:04.680 --> 31:06.080
Or this is going to be
a real short ride.

31:06.400 --> 31:07.550
God damn it!

31:10.040 --> 31:11.156
MILLER: <i>Holden!</i>

31:12.280 --> 31:14.920
Alex, tap the brakes
but do not lose visual.

31:15.000 --> 31:16.275
Jesus... Christ...

31:17.080 --> 31:18.480
(GRUNTING)

31:19.480 --> 31:21.312
(ALL GROANING)

31:26.680 --> 31:28.353
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

31:28.440 --> 31:29.556
- (GRUNTING)
- (BEEPING STOPS)

31:33.320 --> 31:34.800
What the hell
did we accomplish?

31:35.080 --> 31:37.037
You gotta stop following Eros.

31:38.760 --> 31:40.672
It's gonna defend itself,

31:40.760 --> 31:41.989
and my money ain't on you.

31:42.320 --> 31:44.198
I can't do that.
We'll lose it for good.

31:44.480 --> 31:45.914
MILLER: <i>Forget
the goddamn missiles.</i>

31:46.480 --> 31:48.676
She'll dodge those just like
she did the <i>Nauvoo,</i>

31:49.320 --> 31:50.640
or something
a lot worse.

31:51.400 --> 31:54.199
Hoss, I'm losing visual...

31:54.840 --> 31:56.991
MILLER: <i>Your crew
is gonna die for nothing.</i>

31:57.480 --> 32:00.154
Back off now. Find a way
to divert those missiles.

32:00.600 --> 32:02.319
And then what? What?

32:02.920 --> 32:04.593
I'll try to
reach Julie,

32:04.920 --> 32:06.832
if there's any part
of her still left.

32:07.520 --> 32:08.954
Get her to stop this rock.

32:09.680 --> 32:10.750
And if that
doesn't work...

32:11.600 --> 32:13.990
(BEEPING STOPS)

32:14.680 --> 32:16.194
I've still got
my little pal here.

32:16.360 --> 32:19.637
You're going to negotiate with a girl
who thinks she's a space station?

32:20.200 --> 32:22.556
When you put it like that
it does sound kinda crazy.

32:23.400 --> 32:25.198
<i>Look, we got one shot here.</i>

32:26.080 --> 32:28.879
<i>You don't back off,
we don't even have that.</i>

32:32.480 --> 32:34.039
(GROANING)

32:39.880 --> 32:41.030
Alex. Power down.

32:42.320 --> 32:43.549
Yes, sir.

32:48.400 --> 32:49.550
(GROANING)

32:55.320 --> 32:56.754
It's all on you now, Miller.

33:02.280 --> 33:03.634
(MONITOR BEEPING)

33:03.720 --> 33:05.359
<i>Long story,
no time for details,</i>

33:05.440 --> 33:07.159
<i>but I'm the one
with the boots on the ground.</i>

33:07.240 --> 33:10.711
<i>Right now it's imperative you divert
Earth's missiles away from Eros.</i>

33:11.400 --> 33:12.754
<i>I'll await confirmation.</i>

33:17.080 --> 33:19.231
The UN's gonna think we're
stealing their missiles

33:19.320 --> 33:21.551
like this whole
thing is a ploy.

33:21.840 --> 33:23.399
They're going
to nuke Tycho next!

33:23.760 --> 33:26.719
- Fred...
- There's no way that I'm going along with this.

33:26.800 --> 33:28.632
It's already done.
They've cut their speed,

33:28.720 --> 33:32.475
the <i>Roci's</i> targeting laser
is off. Eros is gone.

33:41.280 --> 33:43.431
Tell me you know
what you're doing,

33:43.520 --> 33:44.954
you little shit.

33:45.280 --> 33:48.910
We've got guidance control.
I'll take them on a long ride.

34:24.600 --> 34:25.795
Oh, boy.

34:35.480 --> 34:41.431
Well... We made it.
The Blue Falcon.

34:42.320 --> 34:43.639
What are you seeing?

34:44.679 --> 34:46.319
MILLER: (PANTING)
<i>It's kinda beautiful...</i>

34:46.960 --> 34:48.360
HOLDEN: <i>Just get Julie
to stop that rock.</i>

34:48.480 --> 34:50.072
<i>Then we'll come in
and swoop you up.</i>

34:51.560 --> 34:53.074
<i>I guess I'll owe you
that drink.</i>

34:53.360 --> 34:55.351
No, you'll owe me
a bottle, pal.

34:57.400 --> 34:59.392
Hey, uh...

34:59.480 --> 35:03.190
I appreciate you inviting me
into your family there, Holden.

35:03.760 --> 35:05.717
<i>At least you thought
I was worth that.</i>

35:05.800 --> 35:07.200
Yeah, that worked out.

35:13.520 --> 35:15.113
It's time to
see what's what.

35:19.920 --> 35:21.718
- HOLDEN: <i>Hey, Miller...</i>
- (LINE DISCONNECTS)

35:22.400 --> 35:24.039
(BIRD CHIRPING)

35:41.720 --> 35:42.710
What?

36:14.040 --> 36:15.076
Julie?

36:21.160 --> 36:22.958
You need to
wake up now, kid.

36:25.400 --> 36:27.198
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

36:28.400 --> 36:29.595
(BEEPING STOPS)

36:37.920 --> 36:39.070
Hey, can you hear me?

36:40.280 --> 36:42.158
You need to
come back to me now.

36:46.640 --> 36:48.438
(GASPING)

36:48.720 --> 36:49.995
(WHISPERING) Where am I?

36:50.360 --> 36:53.797
You're on Eros, kid.
Eros Station.

36:54.760 --> 36:56.797
It's not
what it used to be.

36:57.680 --> 36:59.672
It's a step up, actually.

37:02.040 --> 37:05.511
What's happened to me?
I don't like it.

37:07.440 --> 37:10.194
Hey, we never really
officially met.

37:10.280 --> 37:11.794
I'm Miller.

37:12.560 --> 37:15.029
I used to be
a cop on Ceres.

37:15.120 --> 37:20.559
I was supposed to find
you and bring you home.

37:20.640 --> 37:21.756
(CLATTERING)

37:23.440 --> 37:24.794
Kidnap job.

37:25.400 --> 37:28.120
Yeah. I kinda
cocked that up, though.

37:28.800 --> 37:31.998
They left me here all alone.
They never came for me.

37:32.520 --> 37:35.797
Listen, Julie,
right now, this station,

37:36.240 --> 37:39.199
this rock is headed
for Earth real fast.

37:39.560 --> 37:42.871
I dreamed that
I was racing.

37:42.960 --> 37:45.270
- Yeah.
- I was going home.

37:45.360 --> 37:49.240
Yeah, we're going to need to stop that,
Jules.

37:49.320 --> 37:50.834
No.

37:51.320 --> 37:53.198
You can't take
the <i>Razorback.</i>

37:53.400 --> 37:56.393
You never took shit
from anyone, did you?

37:59.600 --> 38:02.320
But you're driving
this bus, Julie.

38:02.880 --> 38:04.234
Do you know that?

38:04.360 --> 38:06.079
I miss Earth.

38:06.440 --> 38:07.430
I know, kid.

38:08.360 --> 38:10.113
But we can't go to Earth.

38:10.200 --> 38:13.193
A lot of good people are
gonna die if we go there.

38:13.280 --> 38:15.397
They're the same people
you're fighting for.

38:18.560 --> 38:20.916
(GASPS) I can't
make it stop. It won't stop.

38:21.000 --> 38:23.356
Okay, Julie.
But you gotta try.

38:23.440 --> 38:24.669
JULIE: We can't
stop the work.

38:24.800 --> 38:26.871
All right.
We don't stop the work.

38:27.080 --> 38:30.232
But we don't have
to go to Earth, right?

38:31.240 --> 38:34.631
Why don't we go to Venus?
You were headed that way anyway.

38:34.720 --> 38:37.155
Go to Venus.
Work continues...

38:37.240 --> 38:38.356
I don't think I can.

38:38.720 --> 38:40.393
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

38:50.400 --> 38:51.754
(BEEPING INTENSIFIES)

39:00.160 --> 39:01.560
(BEEPING STOPS)

39:07.560 --> 39:08.550
(GRUNTS)

39:09.480 --> 39:13.110
Look, kid,
I came an awful long way to find you.

39:14.200 --> 39:16.078
Because I
believe in you.

39:16.920 --> 39:18.673
Would you believe
a guy like me

39:19.440 --> 39:21.159
would believe
in something?

39:23.240 --> 39:28.440
I know you're a fighter.
I know you can steer this ship.

39:30.600 --> 39:35.311
I'm done fighting.
I just want to go home.

39:41.880 --> 39:45.794
You can't go home,
Julie. I'm sorry.

39:48.040 --> 39:51.875
We can go anywhere else in the whole
universe, but we can't go home, honey.

39:51.960 --> 39:53.235
Okay?

39:54.240 --> 39:56.357
But, hey,
I need you to know,

39:57.960 --> 40:02.193
whatever happens,
wherever you go,

40:02.760 --> 40:04.353
you're not going
to do it alone.

40:06.920 --> 40:09.435
(DETONATOR BEEPING)

40:10.400 --> 40:12.835
I need you to hold something for me,
okay?

40:13.320 --> 40:15.391
I can't feel my hands.

40:16.720 --> 40:18.996
It's all right.
Right here.

40:19.720 --> 40:22.918
You have beautiful
hands. I got 'em.

40:23.720 --> 40:25.074
Here.

40:26.160 --> 40:27.435
(BEEPING INTENSIFIES)

40:27.520 --> 40:29.830
Just hold this for a minute.
Don't let go.

40:29.920 --> 40:31.354
(BEEPING STOPS)

40:32.560 --> 40:33.960
What is it?

40:35.840 --> 40:36.990
It won't hurt you.

40:46.120 --> 40:48.077
(AIR HISSING)

40:48.920 --> 40:50.513
(BREATHES SHARPLY)

41:18.480 --> 41:19.880
Hey.

41:23.240 --> 41:25.277
(POWERING DOWN)

41:31.720 --> 41:33.234
What happens to us now?

41:34.480 --> 41:38.315
I don't know.
We die, maybe.

41:40.760 --> 41:43.070
But if we don't die,
that'll be interesting.

41:43.880 --> 41:45.837
Whatever happens,
happens to both of us.

41:47.600 --> 41:48.590
It's going to be okay.

41:54.440 --> 41:56.272
You belong with me.
